// Diagram Manager
// CRUD operations for Mermaid diagram files (.mmd) stored in a single directory.

An in-memory index maps diagram IDs to file metadata (path, lastModified).
The index is built at startup by scanning the diagrams directory. File size is
enforced at create and save time using config.MAX_FILE_SIZE.

FUNCTION DiagramManager.constructor(basePath)                                      EXPORT
  Store the base path for diagram storage.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.initialize() -> void
  Ensure the base directory exists, scan for .mmd files, and build the in-memory index
  with path and last-modified timestamp for each file.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.listDiagrams() -> DiagramListItem[]
  Return id, name, and lastModified for every entry in the index.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.getDiagram(id) -> Diagram | null
  Look up the id in the index. IF not found, return null.
  Read and return the file content along with metadata.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.saveDiagram(id, content) -> void
  Throw if id not in index. Throw if content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Write content to file and refresh the lastModified timestamp in the index.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.createDiagram(name, content) -> string
  Sanitize the name to alphanumeric/hyphens/underscores. Throw if id already exists
  or content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE. Write the file, index it, return the id.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.deleteDiagram(id) -> void
  Throw if not found. Delete the file and remove from the index.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.updateIndex(id, path) -> void
  Asynchronously stat the file and update (or add) the index entry.
  Used by the file watcher to reflect external changes.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.removeFromIndex(id) -> void
  Remove the entry from the in-memory index without touching the file.

---

FUNCTION DiagramManager.reset() -> void
  Clear the entire index. Call initialize() afterward to rebuild for a new storage location.
